  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>Create stunning buildings, offices or something completely different as an Architect. If you love design and want to design housing schemes, one-off properties or landmark buildings like the Shard in London then Architecture is the career for you.</p>
<h2>Career Overview</h2>
<p>Architecture is a creative career which also requires highly technical knowledge. You may create new developments with hundreds of homes, build a completely new property or restore and refurbish an historic building.</p>
<p>You will work with clients to understand their goals and create drawings that will be used by contractors. Architects will usually work on a project from start to finish and work with construction professionals to make sure the build follows the client’s original brief.</p>
<p>As an architect you will have to</p>
<ul>
<li>Use design and engineering skills to</li>
<li>Carry out site visits throughout the project to keep up to date with progress and deal with any issues as they arise</li>
<li>Prepare planning applications and submit them to local authorities</li>
<li>Speak with clients to understand their project and create the initial plans</li>
<li>Understand the local environment and how this will affect the design and build</li>
<li>Project manage contractors, surveyors and other construction professionals</li>
<li>Use computer software to create designs and reports</li>
</ul>
