<h2>Career Prospects</h2>
<p>Architects can progress quickly and will either work for private companies or set up a business. Joining the Royal Institute of British Architects will help you develop your career and progress into a more senior role. </p>
<p>After five years’ experience, architects can be awarded fellow of RIBA status. Most senior architects will set up their own company once they have completed projects and built a reputation. You may choose to specialise in residential, environment, urban or many other areas of expertise.</p>]]></mainContent>
